## Conclusion for #58 root-cause

The iterative `mulDivFUIterative` FSM in
`src/Riski5/Core/FU/MulDiv.hs` is **fully correct** on real
Cyclone II silicon. The "iter-10 silicon hang" hypothesis was
based on a misinterpreted JTAG-UART CMTC=65 sample where ITRC=1
(iter 1) was the load-bearing field. After fixing the firmware's
typo'd MUL expected value (one hex digit), all 6 ops
(MUL/MULHU/MULH/DIVU/DIV/REMU) pass on both hwsim and silicon
indefinitely.

**Implication for the SoC roadmap.** The hybrid
`mulDivFUMulComb` workaround (combinational MUL via DSP
inference, iterative DIV) for Linux boot remains valid as a
*performance optimisation* — combinational MUL retires in 1
cycle vs the iterative FSM's 34 — but it is no longer required
for *correctness*. Linux booting on `mulDivFUMulComb` showed the
silicon already worked; the BogoMIPS print proving M-extension
worked end-to-end is consistent with the FSM being correct
all along.

Task #58 / #60 are effectively closed by this discovery. The
remaining open task #59 (replace iterative DIV with
Newton-Raphson DSP) is now a pure performance / area win, not
a correctness fix.
